The paper deals with directed graph searching and width measures, which are topics that are commonly studied in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses cop and robber games, which are often studied in computational geometry (cs.CG) and game theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper discusses the implications of these width measures for algorithms and complexity, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
